  "market_context": "On 1 November 2023, NQ 1-minute price built a consolidation range around 14624–14640 unable to make new highs or lows, then spiked higher (manipulation) before displacing back into the range, setting up a bullish box setup scenario.",
  "key_observation": "After the manipulation displaced back into the range, rather than entering on the line retest, the analyst waited for an order block to form at the fair value gap — a down-close candle into the FVG followed by a close over it confirmed the long entry.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identify the consolidation: price cannot make new highs/lows, so mark out the lowest bodies of the range as the box.",
    "Mark the accumulation and the subsequent manipulation leg that spiked above the range.",
    "Confirm the manipulation displaces back into the range, validating a box setup.",
    "Note that the original box entry would be on the retest of the upper range line with stop on the manipulation low, but wait for an order block formation instead.",
    "Observe a down-close candle into the fair value gap left by the displacement, marking the bullish order block area.",
    "Wait for a close over that down-close candle to confirm change in state of delivery and enter long.",
    "Place stop on the manipulation low (or alternative low) and project the manipulation leg using standard deviation for targets.",
    "Identify the previous high / fair value gap aligning with the first standard deviation projection as the target."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Patience for an order block confirmation inside the FVG after manipulation gives a higher-probability entry than the raw box-line retest. Combining box setup, OB, FVG and standard deviation projections produces a precise entry, stop, and target structure.",
